BEGIN_PGML For a falling object on Earth, with height measured in feet and time measured in seconds, the curvature coefficient of its height function is (roughly) [`-16\text{.}`]
An object on Earth is shot straight up from a height of [`[$c]`] feet with an initial speed of [`[$c]`] feet per second. How long will it take for the object to land?
